Package: saltbush
Title: Calculating Spectral Diversity From Multi- Or Hyper-spectral Drone Images
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("First", "Last", , "first.last@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-ID"))
Description: saltbush is an R package for processing drone data to calculate spectral diversity metrics. To facilitate testing of the spectral-biodiversity relationship, it also calculates on-the-ground diversity from on-the ground, point-intercept surveys specifically from the AusPlots framework.
